 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-4ga","title":"P7.4 Collision and deduplication tests","description":"# P7.4 Collision and deduplication tests

## Overview
Tests for edge cases where the same session might appear from multiple sources
or where session IDs collide across sources.

## Test Cases

### Same Session from Multiple Sources
```rust
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_same_session_different_sources() {
    // Scenario: User syncs from laptop, then laptop syncs same session later
    // Each should be treated as separate if sync timestamps differ

    let session_id = "conv_abc123";

    // First sync
    let first_sync = create_session_fixture(session_id, "laptop", Utc::now() - Duration::hours(2));
    indexer.add_root(&first_sync, Provenance::remote_with_timestamp("laptop".into(), Utc::now() - Duration::hours(2)));
    indexer.index_all().await.unwrap();

    // Second sync (updated content)
    let second_sync = create_session_fixture(session_id, "laptop", Utc::now());
    indexer.add_root(&second_sync, Provenance::remote_with_timestamp("laptop".into(), Utc::now()));
    indexer.index_incremental().await.unwrap();

    // Should have only one entry (updated)
    let results = searcher.search_by_id(session_id).await.unwrap();
    assert_eq!(results.len(), 1);
    assert_eq!(results[0].sync_timestamp, Some(Utc::now()));  // Latest sync
}

#[tokio::test]
async fn test_same_id_different_sources_are_distinct() {
    // Scenario: Two different machines happen to have sessions with same ID
    // (unlikely with UUIDs but possible with sequential IDs)

    let session_id = "session_001";

    // Local session
    let local = create_session_fixture(session_id, "local", Utc::now());
    indexer.add_root(&local, Provenance::local());

    // Remote session with same ID but different content
    let remote = create_session_fixture_with_content(session_id, "remote", "different content");
    indexer.add_root(&remote, Provenance::remote("laptop".into()));

    indexer.index_all().await.unwrap();

    // Should have TWO entries (distinguished by source)
    let results = searcher.search_all_by_id(session_id).await.unwrap();
    assert_eq!(results.len(), 2);

    // Filter should work
    let local_only = searcher.search_by_id_and_source(session_id, SourceFilter::Local).await.unwrap();
    assert_eq!(local_only.len(), 1);
}
```

### Deduplication Respects Sources
```rust
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_dedup_within_source_not_across() {
    // Same session file indexed twice from same source should dedup
    indexer.add_root(&sessions, Provenance::remote("laptop".into()));
    indexer.index_all().await.unwrap();

    // Index again (simulating re-sync)
    indexer.add_root(&sessions, Provenance::remote("laptop".into()));
    indexer.index_all().await.unwrap();

    // Should still have same count (deduplicated)
    assert_eq!(db.conversation_count().await.unwrap(), sessions.len());
}
```

