 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-4o5f8","title":"Remove dead dismiss_update() function (zero call sites)","description":"## What

Remove the dead dismiss_update() function from src/update_check.rs (lines 221-226).

## CRITICAL: Zero Call Sites

A comprehensive grep of the entire repository confirmed **dismiss_update() is never called anywhere**:
- Not in src/ui/app.rs (TUI)
- Not in src/lib.rs (CLI dispatch)
- Not in any test file
- Not in any integration test
- The only match is the function definition itself at update_check.rs:223

This is dead code, not a stub.

## Current State

```rust
/// Dismiss update banner for this session (doesn't persist skip)
/// Returns true if there was an update to dismiss
pub fn dismiss_update() -> bool {
    // This is handled in-memory by the TUI, not persisted
    true
}
```

## Fix

Delete lines 221-226 (the doc comment and function).

## Testing

Since the function has zero callers, removing it changes zero behavior. The real test is:

1. **Compilation**: cargo check --all-targets passes (no callers → no breakage)
2. **Existing update_check tests**: They don't reference dismiss_update, so they'll pass unchanged
3. **Module integrity test**: Verify the rest of update_check still works:

```rust
#[test]
fn update_check_module_functional_after_dead_code_removal() {
    // dismiss_update() was removed because it had zero call sites and
    // always returned true regardless of state. The rest of the update
    // check module remains fully functional:
    // - check_for_updates(): spawns background HTTP check
    // - skip_update_version(): persists skip decision
    // - UpdateState: manages check cadence + skip list
    //
    // If a TUI dismiss feature is needed in the future, implement it
    // with real state tracking (e.g., checking UpdateState for pending
    // update notifications) rather than a hardcoded true.

    // Verify UpdateState roundtrip (core of the module)
    let state = UpdateState::default();
    assert!(!state.should_check_now(), "default state should not trigger immediate check");
}
```

Run the full module test suite:
